# Node.js Tutorial HTTP Server - Git Ignore Configuration
# Comprehensive ignore patterns for Node.js tutorial application
# Educational HTTP server demonstrating 'Hello World' endpoint

# This file protects sensitive configuration, excludes generated artifacts,
# and maintains clean repository structure for educational purposes

# Key Features:
# - Environment configuration security (.env files)
# - Node.js and npm artifact management (node_modules, logs)
# - Test coverage and quality report exclusion
# - Cross-platform development file handling
# - Security-conscious patterns for credentials and certificates

# Educational Note:
# This tutorial maintains zero external dependencies but includes
# comprehensive patterns for production-ready development workflows

# === Node.js and NPM Artifacts ===
# Package management and Node.js runtime artifacts

# Node.js dependencies (excluded from all levels)
node_modules/

# NPM artifacts and lock files
package-lock.json
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# === Environment Configuration Files ===
# Environment variables and configuration (keep .env.example)

# Environment files containing sensitive configuration
.env
.env.local
.env.development
.env.test
.env.production

# Note: .env.example files remain tracked for setup documentation

# === Test Coverage and Quality Reports ===
# Generated test coverage and quality analysis artifacts

# Coverage reports (generated by test-coverage.js)
coverage/
*.lcov
coverage-summary.json

# Coverage tool outputs
.nyc_output/

# Test results and artifacts
test-results/

# === Application Logs and Runtime Files ===
# Runtime logs, process files, and application artifacts

# Application logs (generated by Logger utility)
*.log
logs/
server.log

# Process runtime files
*.pid

# === Development Environment Files ===
# IDE settings, editor files, and development artifacts

# IDE and editor files
.vscode/
.idea/

# Editor temporary and backup files
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# === Operating System Files ===
# Platform-specific system files and metadata

# macOS system files
.DS_Store

# Windows system files
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# General temporary files
*.tmp

# === Build and Distribution Artifacts ===
# Build outputs and distribution files (tutorial uses zero-build)

# Build and distribution directories
dist/
build/
out/

# === Cache and Temporary Directories ===
# Application caches and temporary processing files

# Cache directories
.cache/

# Temporary directories
tmp/
temp/

# === Security and Authentication Files ===
# Certificates, private keys, and security artifacts

# Security certificates and keys (never commit)
*.pem
*.key
*.p12